      "stimulus": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "An Australian tyre manufacturer is expanding its business. In order to reduce operating costs and increase sales and profit, rubber will be sourced from the global market. \n\nThe business wants to:\n- maintain quality outputs\n- achieve economies of scale."
        }
      ],
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Outline ONE potential issue this business could face in relation to both cost and\nquality of outputs."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 2,
          "stimulus": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ""
            }
          ],
          "is_independent": true,
          "answer": {
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "| Criteria | Marks |\n| -------- | ------- |\n|  - Outlines a potential issue this business could face in relation to both cost and quality of outputs | 2 |\n|  - Provides some relevant information  | 1 |"
              }
            ],
            "summary": "The business can reduce the costs of inputs when they source globally, cheaper inputs such as rubber, may result in lower quality tyres."
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Explain the benefits of achieving economies of scale for both the business and\nconsumers."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 3,
          "is_independent": true,
          "stimulus": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ""
            }
          ],
          "answer": {
            "summary": "Economies of scale will provide this business with cost advantages by increasing the volume of its production, allowing the business to lower the price of the finished product. Consumers will benefit from the reduced price and the business will then increase sales and profits in the\nlong term. ",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "| Criteria | Marks |\n| -------- | ------- |\n|  - Explains the benefits of achieving economies of scale for both the\nbusiness and consumers | 3 |\n|  - Describes the benefit(s) of achieving economies of scale for the business\nand/or consumers  | 2 |\n| -  Provides some relevant information | 1 |"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Explain why both staff and management might be resistant to this change."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 5,
          "stimulus": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The owners of the tyre manufacturing business have purchased leading-edge\ntechnology to help achieve economies of scale."
            }
          ],
          "is_independent": true,
          "answer": {
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "| Criteria | Marks |\n| -------- | ------- |\n| - Provides a thorough explanation of why staff and management in this\nbusiness might be resistant to this change | 5 |\n| - Provides a sound explanation of why staff and management in this\nbusiness might be resistant to this change | 4 |\n|  - Demonstrates some understanding of why staff and/or management in\nthis business might be resistant to this change  | 3 |\n|  - Identifies why staff and/or management in this business might be\nresistant to this change  | 2 |\n| -  Provides some relevant information | 1 |"
              }
            ],
            "summary": "The leading-edge technology purchased would be costly for management. The new technology may also require staff and management to be retrained. This can be expensive for management and staff may be resistant to learning new techniques due to fear or inertia.\nFear of job loss may cause resistance to change as staff may feel that processes may become automated and their jobs may become redundant. This also imposes extra costs to the business. "
          }
        }
      ]
    },
